	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-DR-19390127_EN1.jpg"/>
			<p><!-- <persName ref="#_1">North Winship</persName>, Proposals looking to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">anti-Jewish
          legislation</term>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>, <date when="1939-01-27">January 27, 1939</date>, p. 1-3, 5-6. National Archives II, RG 59, Records
        of the Department of State relating to internal affairs of Poland 1916-1944, Washington,
        D.C. 1981 (Microfilm): Doc. 860C.4016/583.--></p>
			<p>I have the honor to refer to despatch No. 866, dated <date when="1938-12-27">December 27, 1938</date>, which in the last paragraph on
				page 2 mentions the growing tendency among certain politicians to enact <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">anti-Jewish legislation</term>, and to report that
				this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-956" type="subject">movement</term> is gaining momentum. In fact,
				at the beginning of the present budget session of the <orgName ref="#ehri_dr_parliament_polish">Parliament</orgName> early in
				December, Deputy <persName ref="#ehri_et_stoch_franciszek">Stoch</persName> informed the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">press</term> that he had worked out a concrete
				proposal embodying <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">anti-Jewish legislation</term>
				which he wished to present. […]</p>
			<pb n="2" facs="EHRI-DR-19390127_EN2.jpg"/>
			<p>Deputy <persName ref="#ehri_et_stoch_franciszek">Stoch</persName> project is based not so much on <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-328" type="subject">racial</term> but on <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-592" type="subject">religious principles</term> and proposes the extension
				of only <q>temporary <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-659" type="subject">citizenship</term></q> [sic] to
				all professed <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>, including even those who
				changed their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-724" type="subject">religion</term> as far back as <date
					when="1918">1918</date>. Under his project these <q>temporary citizens</q> would <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-659" type="subject">lose</term>: Their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1059" type="subject">political rights</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-897" type="subject">Employment in public service institutions</term> and
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134" type="subject">schools</term>, with the exception of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-879" type="subject">Jewish private schools</term>, Title to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1086" type="subject">military service</term>, Right to handle <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-897" type="subject">public service</term> supplies, Right to perform
				licensed professions, Right to publish and collaborate in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html"
					>Polish</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">press organs</term>, Right to own and operate
				advertising offices.</p>
			<p>Furthermore the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">bill</term> provides that pensions
				and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-941" type="subject">insurance</term> fees paid up to date by these
				citizens would be returned to them. Full <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1059" type="subject"
					>citizenship rights</term> would be enjoyed only by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864"
					type="subject">Jews</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-803" type="subject">converted to Christianity</term> before the
				restoration of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland’s</placeName> independence, as well as
					<pb n="3" facs="EHRI-DR-19390127_EN3.jpg"/>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> having special merits because of their
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-884" type="subject">service during the war</term> or because of
				their outstanding work for <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>. […]</p>
			<pb n="5" facs="EHRI-DR-19390127_EN5.jpg"/>
			<p>As was pointed out in my despatch No. 560 of <date when="1938-01-24">January 24, 1938</date> (<term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">Anti-Jewish Legislation</term>), it is still true, as
				was then the case, that the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> feels that the time is not ripe
				yet for the enactment of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">anti-Jewish
					legislation</term> as such. However, the significant point in this report is that the tendency and trend of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1072" type="subject">public opinion</term> is in that direction. In the
				meantime the Government still endeavors to side-step the main issue, but working through <orgName ref="#ehri_dr_ozon&gt;"
					>OZON</orgName>, continues its <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-594" type="subject">policy</term> of
				guarded <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-649" type="subject">discrimination</term>, limiting <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term> activity wherever possible without
				direct <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-328" type="subject">racial</term> reference. Temporizing in this
				manner, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> hopes to avoid hostile
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1022" type="subject">foreign censure</term>, placate <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-329" type="subject">anti-Jewish</term> circles here, and not to arouse
				Jewish apprehension or enmity. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term>
				is under no illusion, however, but that eventually this issue will have to be faced squarely.</p>
